# Common failures — startup & libraries

Cluster won't start → **Event Log** tab is the source of truth.

## Startup — four modes

- `InstanceLimitExceeded` → **cloud quota/capacity** → new type/AZ, quota, **serverless**
- `NotAuthorizedToAssumeRole` / 403 → **IAM** → fix role trust + policies
- `INIT_SCRIPT_FAILURE` → read init log, fix (no init scripts on serverless)
- Library install → **Libraries** tab → remove / pin

## Library conflicts

- **Notebook-scoped `%pip install`** — own env per notebook
- **Pin versions** (`mypkg==2.4.1`) · **DBR ML runtime** · **serverless**

**Tells:** `InstanceLimitExceeded` = quota (not memory) · shared-cluster collision → **notebook-scoped `%pip`**.
